Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code within the curly braces will be executed. For example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is true
}
```

In this example, if the age variable is greater than or equal to 18, the code within the curly braces will be executed. If the condition is false, the code within the curly braces will not be executed.
